&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Section 5.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Section 5 of the Citizenship Act, 1955 allows individuals to acquire Indian citizenship through registration.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This section applies to certain specified categories, including persons of Indian origin who reside in India for a prescribed period.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Spouses of Indian citizens&lt;/strong&gt; and minor children of Indian citizens are also eligible for citizenship through registration under this section.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The process involves submitting an application, fulfilling the residency requirements, and meeting other conditions as prescribed by the Act.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Section 6:&lt;/strong&gt; This section deals with acquiring Indian citizenship through naturalization. Citizenship by naturalization is granted to foreign nationals who meet specific criteria, including residing in India for a minimum of 12 years and fulfilling other conditions as prescribed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Section 3:&lt;/strong&gt; Section 3 defines citizenship by birth. It specifies that individuals born in India on or after January 26, 1950, but before July 1, 1987, are considered Indian citizens. For individuals born after July 1, 1987, at least one parent must be an Indian citizen.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Section 4:&lt;/strong&gt; This section governs citizenship by descent. It provides that individuals born outside India are considered Indian citizens if either parent is an Indian citizen at the time of the individual&amp;#39;s birth. Certain additional conditions apply for individuals born after December 10, 1992.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Citizenship Act, 1955:&lt;/strong&gt; The Citizenship Act, 1955, is the primary legislation governing the acquisition, termination, and determination of Indian citizenship. It provides multiple modes of acquiring citizenship, including birth, descent, registration, and naturalization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To organise village panchayat&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directive Principles of State Policy (DPSP)&lt;/strong&gt; are enshrined in &lt;strong&gt;Part IV&lt;/strong&gt; of the Indian Constitution (Articles 36 to 51). They aim to create social and economic conditions under which citizens can lead a good life.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The principle to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;organise village panchayats&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is mentioned in &lt;strong&gt;Article 40&lt;/strong&gt; of the Indian Constitution and is inspired by &lt;strong&gt;Gandhian principles&lt;/strong&gt;. Gandhiji strongly advocated for decentralized governance through Panchayati Raj institutions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The directive to &amp;quot;organise village panchayats and endow them with powers and authority to function as units of self-government&amp;quot; reflects the idea of &lt;strong&gt;Gram Swaraj&lt;/strong&gt; (self-rule), a concept central to Gandhian philosophy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Other Gandhian principles found in the DPSP include the promotion of cottage industries, prohibition of intoxicating drinks, and prevention of slaughter of cows and calves, all of which align with his vision for a self-sufficient rural economy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Options like &amp;quot;to secure the right to adequate means of livelihood&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;to secure equal pay for men and women&amp;quot; are based on &lt;strong&gt;socio-economic principles&lt;/strong&gt; rather than Gandhian values. Similarly, &amp;quot;to promote international peace&amp;quot; aligns with the ideals of international cooperation but is not specifically rooted in Gandhian ideology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 40 and Panchayati Raj:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Article 40 directs the state to take steps to organise village panchayats and provide them with adequate powers to function as self-governing institutions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;73rd Constitutional Amendment Act of 1992&lt;/strong&gt; gave constitutional status to Panchayati Raj institutions, implementing the Gandhian vision of decentralised governance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Panchayati Raj now forms a three-tier system in rural India, consisting of the Gram Panchayat (village level), Panchayat Samiti (block level), and Zila Parishad (district level).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gandhian Principles in DPSP:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Promotion of cottage industries:&lt;/strong&gt; Article 43 suggests the state should promote cottage industries in rural areas to enhance self-reliance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prohibition of intoxicating substances:&lt;/strong&gt; Article 47 directs the state to work towards the prohibition of consumption of intoxicating drinks and drugs harmful to health.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prevention of slaughter of cows:&lt;/strong&gt; Article 48 calls for the preservation of cattle wealth, including cows and calves, reflecting Gandhiji&amp;rsquo;s emphasis on protecting livestock.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Classification of DPSPs:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Socialistic Principles:&lt;/strong&gt; These aim to promote social and economic justice, for example, ensuring equal pay for equal work (Article 39).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gandhian Principles:&lt;/strong&gt; Principles inspired by Mahatma Gandhi&amp;#39;s philosophy, such as village panchayats and promotion of cottage industries.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liberal-Intellectual Principles:&lt;/strong&gt; These include provisions for protecting the environment, promoting international peace, and ensuring uniform civil codes.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important Acts related to Panchayati Raj:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Balwant Rai Mehta Committee (1957):&lt;/strong&gt; Recommended the establishment of the Panchayati Raj system.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;73rd Amendment Act (1992):&lt;/strong&gt; Provided constitutional status to Panchayati Raj institutions, making them a part of the governance structure.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eleventh Schedule:&lt;/strong&gt; Introduced through the 73rd Amendment, it lists 29 functional items assigned to Panchayats.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Coromandel.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coromandel Coast -&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;It is the name given to the &lt;strong&gt;southeast coastline&lt;/strong&gt; of the &lt;strong&gt;Indian peninsula.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The eastern coastal plain between the Godavari and the Mahanadi is known as &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Northern Circars&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​The West Coast Plain is divided into &lt;strong&gt;three parts -&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The northern part of the coast is known as &lt;strong&gt;Konkan (Mumbai-Goa),&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The middle section is called&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Kannada Coast&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The southern section is called the&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Malabar Coast&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the northern part of the West Coastal Plain lies the &lt;strong&gt;Gulf of Khambat&lt;/strong&gt; and the &lt;strong&gt;Gulf of Kutch.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Option 4.&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;69th &lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Constitutional Amendment Act of 1991&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;69 Amendment Constitutional Amendment Act of 1991 designated the&lt;strong&gt; Union Territory of Delhi as the National Capital Territory of Delhi.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The 69th Amendment act of the&lt;strong&gt; Indian Constitution granted special status to Delhi i&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;n 1991&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;it was&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;declared the National Capital Territory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It &lt;strong&gt;created a state assembly and council &lt;/strong&gt;of ministers for the state.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aditya Nath Jha became the first Lieutenant Governor &lt;/strong&gt;of Delhi under the act.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Article 239AA of the Constitution gave the status of Union Territory to Delhi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ashwagandha.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align:middle;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prime Minister Narendra Modi released a commemorative postal stamp during the Second WHO Global Summit on Traditional Medicine.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The event was held at Bharat Mandapam, New Delhi, on 19 December 2025.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align:middle;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The commemorative postage stamp was released on Ashwagandha.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ashwagandha is scientifically known as Withania somnifera.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The stamp has a denomination of ₹5.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It was designed by the Department of Posts in collaboration with the Ministry of Ayush.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align:middle;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ashwagandha&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; is a key medicinal herb used in Ayurveda for stress relief, immunity and vitality.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Second WHO Global Summit on Traditional Medicine was jointly organised by WHO and the Ministry of Ayush.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The summit was held from 17&amp;ndash;19 December 2025 in New Delhi.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The release highlights India&amp;rsquo;s efforts to promote traditional medicine globally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alt + Tab.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

