&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chief Justice of India&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Chief Election Commissioner (CEC) and Other Election Commissioners (ECs), (Appointment, Conditions of Service and Term of Office) Bill, 2023 was introduced in the Rajya Sabha.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This Bill seeks to change the composition of the panel that selects the CEC and ECs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Under the new Bill, the Chief Justice of India (CJI) would be removed from the selection committee.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Previously, the selection panel included the Prime Minister, the Leader of the Opposition, and the Chief Justice of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Bill proposes to replace the Chief Justice of India with a nominated Union Cabinet Minister.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Election Commission of India (ECI)&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Established in 1950, the ECI is a constitutional body responsible for administering election processes in India at both national and state levels.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The ECI ensures the conduct of free and fair elections to the Parliament, State Legislatures, and the offices of the President and Vice President in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The ECI operates under the authority of the Constitution per Article 324.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Composition of the Election Commission&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Election Commission consists of the Chief Election Commissioner and two other Election Commissioners.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The CEC and ECs have equal powers and receive equal salaries, allowances, and other perquisites.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;However, in case of difference of opinion amongst the CEC and/or two other ECs, the matter is decided by the Commission by a majority.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appointment Process of CEC and ECs&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Previously, the appointment of the CEC and other ECs was made by the President based on the recommendations of a committee consisting of the Prime Minister, the Leader of the Opposition, and the Chief Justice of India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The new Bill proposes to replace the Chief Justice of India with a nominated Union Cabinet Minister in the selection committee.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role and Functions of the Election Commission&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The ECI is responsible for preparing electoral rolls and updating the voter list.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It supervises the conduct of elections, ensuring they are free, fair, and in accordance with the law.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The ECI also enforces the Model Code of Conduct and addresses grievances related to the election process.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is option &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; i.e&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Database Management System&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Database Management System:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;database management system (DBMS) or database system&lt;/strong&gt;, in short, is a software that can be used &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to create, manage and&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;controls access to the data stored in the database&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;. Hence option 1 is correct.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It&amp;nbsp;lets users create a database, store, manage, update/modify and retrieve data from that database by users or application programs.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Some examples of open source and commercial DBMS include &lt;strong&gt;MySQL, Oracle, PostgreSQL, SQL Server, Microsoft Access, MongoDB.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;​&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;File system:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;A file system is a process that manages how and where data on a storage disk,&lt;strong&gt; typically a hard disk drive (HDD), is stored, accessed and managed&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;It is a logical disk component that manages a disk&amp;#39;s internal operations as it relates to a computer and is abstract to a human user.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A file can be understood as a container to store data in a computer.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Contents of a file can be texts, computer program code, comma-separated values&amp;nbsp;(CSV)&amp;nbsp;etc. &lt;strong&gt;Likewise, pictures, audios/videos, web pages&lt;/strong&gt; are also files.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network Management System (NMS):&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It&amp;nbsp;is a system designed for &lt;strong&gt;monitoring, maintaining, and optimizing a network&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It includes both hardware and software, but most often an NMS refers to the software used to manage a network. It also&amp;nbsp;provides multiple services.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operating System:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It&amp;nbsp;is an interface between a computer user and computer hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;An operating system is a software which performs all the basic tasks like &lt;strong&gt;file management, memory management, process management, handling input and output, and controlling peripheral devices such as disk drives and printers&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is option &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;2&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; i.e. &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Vajji&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Licchavis &lt;/strong&gt;were a clan amongst the &lt;strong&gt;Vajji Mahajanapada &lt;/strong&gt;of ancient India.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vaishali&lt;/strong&gt;, the&lt;strong&gt; capital and homeland of the Licchavis&lt;/strong&gt;, was also the capital of the Vajji mahajanapada.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;It was later occupied by &lt;strong&gt;Ajatashatru&lt;/strong&gt;, who annexed the Vajji territory into his kingdom &lt;strong&gt;during the Magadha-Vajji war.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;The Mahājanapadas were sixteen kingdoms or oligarchic republics that existed in ancient India from the sixth to fourth centuries BCE.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;Vajji or Vrijji was a confederacy of neighboring clans including the Licchavis and one of the principal mahājanapadas of Ancient India.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;The area they ruled constitutes the region of Mithila in northern Bihar and their capital was the city of Vaishali.&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Mahajanpadas:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;These massive Indian cities were home to the 16 great kingdoms described in the ancient texts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;In the modern era, the term &amp;lsquo;mahajanapadas&amp;rsquo; is often used to refer to the 16 great kingdoms.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;In the sixth century BC, present-day Bihar and eastern Uttar Pradesh became centers of political activities as the region was not only fertile but also closer to the iron production centers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Iron production played a crucial role in expanding the territorial states of the region.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;These expansions helped some of these &amp;lsquo;janapadas&amp;rsquo; turn into large states or &amp;lsquo;mahajanapadas.&amp;rsquo; Most of these &amp;lsquo;mahajanapadas&amp;rsquo; were monarchical in nature, while some of them were democratic states.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Many prominent ancient Buddhist texts make frequent references to the &amp;lsquo;16 great kingdoms&amp;rsquo; (mahajanapadas) that flourished between the sixth and the fourth centuries BCE.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;These 16 kingdoms included kingdoms like Anga, Gandhara, Kuru, and Panchala, which are mentioned in the great Indian epic &amp;lsquo;Mahabharata.&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;All of them Magadh Janapada was the Most Important in ancient history.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;List of Mahajanapadas:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Magadha:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Magadha was one of the most prosperous kingdoms of ancient India and one of the most prominent &amp;lsquo;mahajanapadas.&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;For many years, Pataliputra was the capital of Magadha.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The kingdom was bounded by the Ganges in the north, river Champa in the east, and river Son in the west.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;According to ancient texts, Brihadratha was the earliest known ruler of Magadha.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The kingdom was also ruled by King Bimbisara, under whom Magadha flourished.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Great Indian empires including the famous Maurya Dynasty originated in Magadha.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Gautama Buddha spent much of his life in Magadha, hence the region is believed to hold great significance to Buddhists.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Gandhara:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;This great kingdom was served graciously by the river Indus and its capital Taksashila (Taxila) housed the renowned center of learning, the &amp;lsquo;Taksashila University.&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Scholars came to the university from all over the world in order to seek greater knowledge and wisdom.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Kamboja:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;It is said that ancient Kamboja was located on either side of the Hindukush mountain range.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;But clans of Kamboja are believed to have crossed the mountain range to plant colonies in the southern side as well.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Kuru:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;At the time of the Budhha, Kuru was ruled by Korayvya, a titular chieftain.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Its capital was Indraprastha (present-day Delhi), which was known for people with sound health and deep wisdom.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Kosala:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The kingdom of Kosala was located close to the kingdom of Magadha.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;With Ayodhya as its capital, Kosala was bound by the river Ganges in the south, river Gandak in the east, and the Himalaya mountains in the north.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Malla:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The Mallas of the Malla kingdom is often described as powerful people who dwelled in Northern South Asia.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Panchala:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The Panchala kingdom was located east of the Kuru kingdom, between the river Ganges and the mountain ranges of the Himalayas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Panchala was divided into two parts, namely Dakshina-Panchala and Uttara-Panchala.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Matsya:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Located south of the Kuru kingdom and west of river Yamuna, the Matsya kingdom was founded by an Indo-Aryan tribe of the Vedic age.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Chedi:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The kingdom of Chedi finds great prominence in the Hindu epic Mahabharata.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;According to the ancient text, Chedi was ruled by a king named Shishupala, who was an ally of the kings from Magadha and Kuru.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Anga:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The earliest references to the people of Anga are made in the &amp;lsquo;Atharva Veda,&amp;rsquo; which describes the Angas as despised people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(76, 74, 74); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The &amp;lsquo;Jaina Prajnapana&amp;rsquo; claims that Angas was among the earliest groups of Aryan people.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Avanti:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Avanti was a very important kingdom located in Western India and was considered to be one of the four important monarchies during the time Buddhism began in India.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Vamsa / Vatsa:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Considered to be an offshoot of the Kurus, the kingdom of Vatsa or Vamsa was roughly situated at the location of modern-day Allahabad in Uttar Pradesh.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The capital city was known as Kaushambi, which was a prosperous city.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Kasi:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The Aryans who had settled around Varanasi were known as Kasis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The city was flanked by the rivers Varuna and Asi from which the place derives its name.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Kasi was the most powerful kingdom of the sixteen Janapadas before the rise of Buddhism.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;During the rise of Buddha, it was converted into Kosala.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;This place is mentioned as Kausika / Kausaka in the Matsya Purana.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Surasena:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The location of the Surasena was around the west side of the river Yamuna and had its capital city at Mathura.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The king of Surasena, Avantiputra played a vital role in promoting Buddhism in his kingdom.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Vajji / Vrije:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The Vajji or Vriji comprised eight to nine allied races and this kingdom became an important center of cultural and political activities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;It was essentially located in northern India.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Out of the nine races, the Licchhavis, the Vedehans, the Jnatrikas, and the Vajjis were the most important.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Assaka / Ashmaka:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Assaka, also known as Ashmaka was a kingdom that was located in the south of India.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;During the time of Buddha, this tribe was located on the banks of the river Godavari.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The capital city of Assaka was known as Potana.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700; text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Vamsa / Vatsa:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Considered to be an offshoot of the Kurus, the kingdom of Vatsa or Vamsa was roughly situated at the location of modern-day Allahabad in Uttar Pradesh.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(44, 44, 44); text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The capital city was known as Kaushambi, which was a prosperous city.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reduction in tax rates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expansionary fiscal policy&lt;/strong&gt; is implemented during a &lt;strong&gt;recession&lt;/strong&gt; to stimulate economic activity and increase aggregate demand.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;One of the primary methods of expansionary fiscal policy is &lt;strong&gt;reducing tax rates&lt;/strong&gt;. Lower taxes increase disposable income for consumers, encouraging spending and boosting demand in the economy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;This statement is correct.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sale of government securities&lt;/strong&gt; is not a part of expansionary fiscal policy. Instead, it is associated with monetary policy tools to manage liquidity and interest rates.&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;This statement is incorrect.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Repo rate increase&lt;/strong&gt; is a monetary policy tool used by central banks to control inflation. Increasing repo rates discourages borrowing and reduces liquidity in the economy, which is not suitable during a recession.&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;This statement is incorrect.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Restrictions on lending&lt;/strong&gt; are counterproductive during a recession. An expansionary fiscal policy aims to encourage borrowing and spending, not restrict it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;This statement is incorrect.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expansionary Fiscal Policy:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Expansionary fiscal policy refers to measures taken by the government to increase economic activity during times of slowdown or recession.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It often involves &lt;strong&gt;reducing taxes&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;increasing government spending&lt;/strong&gt;, or a combination of both to stimulate demand and production.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This policy aims to combat unemployment, reduce the output gap, and boost economic growth.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tax Rate Reduction:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Lowering tax rates increases the disposable income available to individuals and businesses, encouraging higher consumption and investment.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;For instance, during the 2008 financial crisis, several countries implemented tax cuts as part of their fiscal stimulus packages.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Expansionary Measures:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Government spending:&lt;/strong&gt; Direct expenditure on infrastructure projects, healthcare, education, and welfare programs boosts employment and demand.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Examples include stimulus packages such as the &lt;strong&gt;American Recovery and Reinvestment Act (2009)&lt;/strong&gt; during the Great Recession.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monetary Policy vs Fiscal Policy:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monetary policy&lt;/strong&gt; involves regulating the money supply and interest rates, often managed by central banks.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fiscal policy&lt;/strong&gt; deals with government spending and taxation. While monetary policy impacts liquidity, fiscal policy directly influences demand.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Characteristics of Expansionary Fiscal Policy:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Focuses on &lt;strong&gt;reducing unemployment&lt;/strong&gt; and increasing economic output.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;May lead to a &lt;strong&gt;budget deficit&lt;/strong&gt; as government spending exceeds revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Should be carefully managed to prevent long-term inflation or excessive debt accumulation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Examples of Fiscal Stimulus:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;New Deal&lt;/strong&gt; in the United States during the 1930s aimed to revive the economy through public works projects.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;During the COVID-19 pandemic, countries worldwide implemented fiscal stimulus measures to support businesses and individuals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt; 16.68%&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;literacy rate in the country is 74.04 per cent,&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;82.14 for males and 65.46 for females.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The national literacy rate, according to the 2011 census, was&lt;strong&gt; 74.04 percent.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Census 2011 defines a literate person as, &amp;ldquo;a person aged seven and above who can both read and write with understanding in any language, is treated as literate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Among the Indian states, &lt;strong&gt;Kerala has the highest literacy rate 93.91% &lt;/strong&gt;and then &lt;strong&gt;Mizoram 91.58%.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As per the 2011 census, among states, &lt;strong&gt;Bihar has the lowest literacy rate of 61.8%.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The literacy rate went up from 64.83% in 2001 to 74.04% in 2011 showing an increase of 9.21%. Interestingly, females literacy level saw a significant jump as compared to males between 2001-2011. While female literacy in 2001 stood at 53.67%, it has gone up to 65.46% in 2011.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;land gifted to Brahmans&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); font-size: var(--bs-body-font-size); font-weight: var(--bs-body-font-weight); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;During the &lt;strong&gt;Chola period, &amp;quot;Brahmadeya&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;was a type of &lt;strong&gt;land that was gifted to Brahmans &lt;/strong&gt;as a form of religious endowment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This land was considered sacred and was exempt from taxes and other obligations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The purpose of such endowments was to ensure the welfare of the Brahmans and to earn religious merit for the donors.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The other options are not correct because &amp;quot;land of non-Brahmana peasant proprietors&amp;quot; was known as &amp;quot;grama&amp;quot; and was subject to taxes and other obligations. &amp;quot;Land gifted to temples&amp;quot; was known as &amp;quot;devadana&amp;quot; and was also exempt from taxes but was not exclusively for Brahmans. &amp;quot;Land of royal person&amp;quot; was known as &amp;quot;rajakulam&amp;quot; and was under the control of the king.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Brahmans were the highest caste in the Hindu social hierarchy and were traditionally associated with priestly and scholarly roles.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Religious endowments were a common practice in ancient India and were used to support various religious institutions and individuals.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The practice of Brahmans receiving land as endowments continued well into the medieval period and beyond.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The concept of &amp;quot;Brahmadeya&amp;quot; reflects the importance of land as a form of wealth and power in ancient India.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Supercomputers&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supercomputers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A supercomputer is a computer that performs at or near the currently highest operational rate for computers.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is used for scientific and engineering applications that must handle very large databases or do a great amount of computation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They were introduced in the 1960s.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The US has long been the leader in the supercomputer field.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Examples of special-purpose supercomputers include Belle, Deep Blue, and Hydra.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Servers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A server is a computer that provides data to other computers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It may serve data to systems on a local area network or a wide area network over the Internet.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Many types of servers exist, including web servers, mail servers, and file servers.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Each type runs software specific to the purpose of the server.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A single server can serve multiple clients, and a single client can use multiple servers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Laptops&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A laptop is a small, portable personal computer with a screen and alphanumeric keyboard.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Laptops combine all the input/output components and capabilities of a desktop computer, including the display screen, small speakers, a keyboard, data storage device, sometimes an optical disc drive, pointing devices with an operating system, a processor, and memory into a single unit.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mainframes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A mainframe computer is a computer used primarily by large organizations for critical applications, bulk data processing.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A mainframe computer is larger and has more processing power than some other classes of computers, such as minicomputers, servers, workstations, and personal computers.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Modern mainframes can run multiple different instances of operating systems at the same time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Altitude difference&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ooty is located at an altitude of approximately 2,240 meters above sea level, while Coimbatore is situated at a much lower altitude of approximately 411 meters.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As altitude increases, the temperature decreases due to the thinning of the atmosphere and reduced air pressure, a phenomenon governed by the lapse rate (average decrease of temperature by 6.5&amp;deg;C per 1,000 meters of elevation).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ooty&amp;rsquo;s elevated location in the Nilgiri Hills results in cooler temperatures compared to Coimbatore, which is located in a lower-lying plain.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The altitude difference makes Ooty&amp;#39;s climate more temperate and pleasant, while Coimbatore experiences relatively higher temperatures due to its lower elevation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The reduced intensity of solar heating at higher altitudes further contributes to Ooty&amp;rsquo;s cooler climate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proximity to the sea&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;While proximity to the sea influences coastal climates, neither Ooty nor Coimbatore are coastal cities; hence, this factor is irrelevant in explaining their temperature difference.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Regions close to the sea experience moderated temperatures due to the influence of large water bodies. This phenomenon is called maritime influence.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ooty and Coimbatore, being inland cities, are not significantly influenced by the proximity to the sea.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Direction of winds&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The direction of winds can affect local temperatures by transporting warm or cool air masses, but it does not account for the consistent temperature difference between Ooty and Coimbatore.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Seasonal winds such as monsoon winds have a temporary effect on climate but do not explain the year-round cooler climate of Ooty.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desert location&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This option is irrelevant as neither Ooty nor Coimbatore are located in or near desert regions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Deserts are characterized by extreme temperatures due to sparse vegetation and high solar radiation, which does not apply to the geography of Ooty or Coimbatore.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Altitude and Temperature&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Altitude is one of the most important factors influencing temperature; higher altitudes generally lead to cooler temperatures.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The lapse rate explains the temperature decrease with increasing elevation, making hill stations like Ooty naturally cooler than surrounding plains such as Coimbatore.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Geographical features such as mountain ranges and elevation play a significant role in determining local climate conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Committee on Conflicts among Ministers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Appointment Committee of the Cabinet&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Committee on Political Affairs&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Committee on Investment and Growth&lt;/strong&gt; are well-known Cabinet Committees.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;However, there is no such committee named the &lt;strong&gt;Committee on Conflicts among Ministers&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Cabinet Committees are extra-constitutional bodies established by the Prime Minister to reduce the workload of the Cabinet.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They are instrumental in shaping policies and decision-making in various governmental sectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Cabinet Committee on Political Affairs&lt;/strong&gt; is often referred to as the &amp;quot;super-cabinet&amp;quot; as it deals with all major political issues.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Appointment Committee of the Cabinet&lt;/strong&gt; is responsible for appointments to several top posts under the Government of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Committee on Investment and Growth&lt;/strong&gt; focuses on policies aimed at promoting economic growth and investment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These committees are pivotal in ensuring that the Cabinet functions efficiently and effectively by addressing specific areas of governance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barren Island&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Barren Island&lt;/strong&gt; is home to the only active volcano in India, located in the Andaman and Nicobar Islands in the Bay of Bengal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The volcano on Barren Island last erupted in &lt;strong&gt;2017&lt;/strong&gt; and has a history of periodic eruptions, with the first recorded eruption dating back to 1787.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The island is uninhabited due to its volcanic activity, and access is strictly regulated by the Indian government.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The volcanic island is around &lt;strong&gt;3 km in diameter&lt;/strong&gt; and mostly consists of barren, rugged terrain, hence its name.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The volcano is classified as a &lt;strong&gt;stratovolcano&lt;/strong&gt; and is part of the volcanic arc associated with the subduction zone of the Indo-Australian Plate beneath the Eurasian Plate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minicoy Island&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Minicoy is part of the Lakshadweep Islands and is known for its vibrant coral reefs and pristine beaches.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is the second-largest island in Lakshadweep and is renowned for its traditional &amp;quot;Dhoni&amp;quot; boat-making and tuna fishing industries.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Minicoy is not home to any volcanoes, as it is a coral atoll and lacks volcanic origins.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kavaratti Island&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Kavaratti is the capital of Lakshadweep and is famous for its scenic beauty, marine biodiversity, and water sports activities.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The island is a coral island and does not have any volcanic activity.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a major tourist destination and serves as an administrative hub for the Lakshadweep group of islands.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Havelock Island&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Havelock Island, now known as Swaraj Dweep, is part of the Andaman Islands and is a popular tourist destination.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The island is famous for its white-sand beaches, clear waters, and vibrant coral reefs, with Radhanagar Beach being a major attraction.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Unlike Barren Island, Havelock Island does not have any volcanic activity and is inhabited by local communities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Bahadur Shah Zafar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;was deported to Rangoon by the British.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Bahadur Shah Zafar was the second son of Akbar II. He was the last Mughal emperor of India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He reigned&amp;nbsp;for 20 years between 28 September 1837 to 14 September 1857.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He was deported to Burma (presently&amp;nbsp;Myanmar) in the year 1857.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;He died on 7 November 1862 due to illness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cabinet Ministers are a smaller group within the Council of Ministers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 21px; font-weight: bolder; font-family: var(--bs-body-font-family); text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);&quot;&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Council of Ministers in India consists of three categories: &lt;strong&gt;Cabinet Ministers&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Ministers of State&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Deputy Ministers&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cabinet Ministers&lt;/strong&gt; form the core group within the Council of Ministers and are responsible for major ministries such as Finance, Defense, External Affairs, and Home Affairs.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;While &lt;strong&gt;Ministers of State&lt;/strong&gt; assist Cabinet Ministers, they do not have the same rank and authority as Cabinet Ministers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Council of Ministers is appointed by the &lt;strong&gt;President of India&lt;/strong&gt; on the advice of the Prime Minister, not by the Chief Justice.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Not all members of the Council of Ministers are part of the Cabinet; only Cabinet Ministers are included in this smaller, more influential group.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Council of Ministers Structure:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Council of Ministers is headed by the Prime Minister and includes Cabinet Ministers, Ministers of State, and Deputy Ministers.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Cabinet Ministers hold the highest rank and are involved in key decision-making processes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ministers of State may hold independent charge of ministries or assist Cabinet Ministers in their duties.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Deputy Ministers assist both Cabinet and State Ministers in their day-to-day responsibilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cabinet Minister Role:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Cabinet Ministers are responsible for policy formulation and implementation for their respective ministries.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They are part of the Cabinet Committee and play a crucial role in advising the Prime Minister.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Cabinet meets regularly to discuss and decide on matters of national importance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Appointment and Tenure:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The President appoints the Council of Ministers based on the Prime Minister&amp;rsquo;s advice.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Ministers serve at the pleasure of the President, meaning their tenure depends on the support of the Prime Minister.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Prime Minister has the authority to reshuffle portfolios or recommend the removal of ministers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Legislative and Executive Role:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Council of Ministers collectively functions as the executive authority of the government.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Cabinet Ministers represent the government in Parliament and are accountable for their ministries&amp;#39; actions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They introduce bills, budgets, and policies in Parliament for approval and implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India and Russia&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Russia&amp;rsquo;s lower house of parliament has ratified the Reciprocal Exchange of Logistic Support (Relos) Agreement with India, strengthening bilateral defence logistics cooperation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relos is a bilateral military logistics pact enabling mutual use of bases for refueling, maintenance, repairs, training, humanitarian missions, and disaster relief.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The pact reduces paperwork and ensures faster logistical support through rolling settlement of reimbursements.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India gains strategic access to the Arctic region and the Northern Sea Route through Russian bases.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Russia gains access to Indian Ocean facilities, enhancing its reach despite Western sanctions.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Similar Logistics Agreements of India&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;India has similar pacts with the US, UK, Japan, Australia, France, Singapore, South Korea, and Vietnam.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Advantages&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Enhances India&amp;rsquo;s maritime and air mobility across key global routes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Boosts Russia&amp;rsquo;s presence in the Indian Ocean without the need for overseas bases.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Streamlined logistics, faster mission turnaround, simplified documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Promotes joint exercises, disaster relief, and humanitarian missions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Defence Cooperation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Deepens long-standing India&amp;ndash;Russia defence relations and increases operational flexibility for both nations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;South East Africa.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Mediterranean-type vegetation thrives in regions with a specific climate characterized by hot, dry summers and mild, wet winters.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​ &lt;/strong&gt;This climate pattern is typically found around the Mediterranean Sea in Europe, Africa, and Asia.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;California in the United States of America also exhibits a Mediterranean-type climate in some areas, supporting similar vegetation due to comparable weather patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;However, South East Africa (Option 3) does not predominantly host Mediterranean-type vegetation. Instead, this region generally features a different climate, such as a tropical climate with different vegetation types like savannas, forests, and grasslands.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regarding Option 4) in South West Africa, this area also does not feature Mediterranean-type vegetation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It&amp;#39;s characterized by a climate more similar to arid or semi-arid conditions, such as the Namib Desert, which doesn&amp;#39;t support the growth of Mediterranean vegetation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, among the options provided, only Option 4) South West Africa is where you do not typically find Mediterranean-type vegetation due to its arid or semi-arid climate conditions.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
